x4freetext: A pure beam of radioactive Ne-17 ions was produced by
the Spiral facility at GANIL. A beam of O-17 ions was
also produced in the same experimental conditions for
calibration by comparison with the O-17(p,O-17)p
reaction measured in direct kinematics
A fixed 50 mum thick polypropylene C(3)H(6) target
coupled to a second rotating 50 mum thick C(3)H(6)
target. The two targets together were thick enough to
stop the Ne-17 beam.
Scattered protons were detected by a
delta-E-E annular telescope of silicon detectors
placed at forward angles. The telescope was composed of
a thin approx.40 mum double-sided silicon strip
detector coupled to a 1.5 mm thick silicon detector and
was covering angles from 5 to 20 degrees in laboratory
reference frame.
A Multi Channel Plate detector was placed
upstream the target and was used to measure time of
flight and beam intensity.
.Table data were received from Dr.Assie Marlene
for fig.2 of J,PL/B,712,198,2012
